any's success in maintaining economic prosperity and political stability under such challenging conditions has continued to elude observers. Under the editorship of Peter J. Katzenstein, thirteen distinguished scholars from both sides of the Atlantic here provide an original interpretation of the political economy of the Bonn Republic during the forty years since its founding, and explore in particular its extraordinary capacity for accommodating change.Whereas studies in political economy have typically focused on one level of political action—either the shop floor, or national politics, or the international system—this innovative account analyzes the interaction of change at all three levels, bringing together case studies drawn from six manufacturing and service sectors.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aCompetitionzGermany (West). 0aIndustrial managementzGermany (West). 0aIndustrial policyzGermany (West). 0aIndustrieszGermany (West). 4aGeneral Economics. 4aPolitical Science & Political History. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Economy.2bisacsh1 aAllen, Christopher S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBaethge, Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEsser, Josef, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFach, Wolfgang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGowa, Joanne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHalfmann, Jost, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHerrigel, Gary B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJunne, Gerd, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKatzenstein, Peter J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKa